locality: Tumey Hills, along Tumey Hills Access Road ca. 3.5 miles S of entry gate. Head of west facing canyon, along PG&E natural gas pipeline route (Tumey Hills 7.5'Q)

Tumey Hills quad. T15S, R12E, NE1/4 of SE1/4 of sec. 16, elev. 600 ft. In sharp curve of Panoche Rd 2.5 mi west of hwy I-5. Almost bare sandy hill with pieces of gypsum. With dry remains of Amsinkia furcata. Thousands of plants here giving the ground a gray/blue cast. CNPS list 4; a known site.
Fresno County: 9 miles south of Kerman, junction of Madera Ave and MuMullin Grade.
Panoche Hills, ca. 2.4 mi se of Little Panoche Reservoir
